            [
                'title' => 'Shooting of Donnell Thompson, Jr.',
                'posted_by' => 'Cochran Firm California',
                'image' => 'storage/news/news2.webp',
                'short_description' => 'In July of 2016, LA County Special Enforcement Bureau deputies shot and killed and unarmed civilian, 27 year-old Donnell Thompson, Jr., while searching for an armed suspect in a nearby car jacking incident.',
                'description' => '<p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 1em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 19px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline;  color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: Montserrat; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 500; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">In July of 2016, LA County&nbsp;Special Enforcement Bureau&nbsp;deputies&nbsp;shot and killed and unarmed civilian, 27 year-old Donnell Thompson, Jr., while searching for an armed suspect in a nearby car jacking incident. &nbsp;Members of&nbsp;the SEB surrounded Mr. Thompson, a mentally disabled man, and then shot him from atop an armored vehicle with a high powered military style rifle. &nbsp;The SEB is a unit similar to SWAT units found in other law enforcement agencies.</p><p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 1em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 19px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline;  color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: Montserrat; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 500; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">The family was awarded a settlement of over $1.5 million after motions were filed on behalf of the family by Brian Dunn of the Cochran Firm.</p><p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 19px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline;  color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: Montserrat; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 500; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Read the full Los Angels Times&nbsp;article here:&nbsp;<a href="http://www.latimes.com/local/lanow/la-me-ln-thompson-shooting-settlement-20170906-story.html" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 19px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; text-decoration: none; color: rgb(229, 196, 101) !important;">Read More</a></p>',
